# Trivy ignore file — accepted IaC misconfigurations, with justification.
# Reviewed for the MenuScan graduation project (single demo environment).

# AVD-GCP-0017 — Cloud SQL instance has a public IP address.
#
# Accepted (deferred), rationale:
#   - Cloud Run reaches the database through the managed Cloud SQL Auth Proxy,
#     which connects to the instance via this public IP over an encrypted,
#     IAM-authenticated tunnel — not a plaintext connection.
#   - Removing the public IP (ipv4_enabled = false) would require provisioning
#     Private IP + a VPC connector for Cloud Run first; doing that mid-project
#     risks breaking the live DB connection, so it is deferred.
#   - TLS is now enforced on the instance (ssl_mode = ENCRYPTED_ONLY), which
#     addresses the related AVD-GCP-0015 finding for real.
AVD-GCP-0017
